      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Leafs' season-long freefall hit terminal velocity Sunday night, when they <strong>blew a late lead in a 6-5 heartbreaker to Dallas</strong>, capping a home finale that encapsulated every chaotic twist of this 32-35-14 disaster&mdash;now 8th in the Atlantic, 15th in the East, with 78 points and a six-game skid that has them 35 games back and firmly e for elimination. Goals against are hemorrhaging at 3.61 per game, the league's sieve, while the offense sputters at 3.10; William Nylander's 77 points (29 goals, 48 assists) remain the lone beacon in this dim firmament, but even he can't drag John Tavares's creaky 71 points or a defense that's forgotten how to clear its zone. The captain's line looks lost, penalties mount, and the tank's bottom is in sight&mdash;no one's whispering playoffs anymore. Tonight's road tilt against the Senators at Canadian Tire Centre offers zero illusions: Ottawa's owned them lately (Leafs 1-5-0 in recent battles), and Linus Ullmark's .890 save clip awaits. <strong>Watch if Woll can steal one&mdash;or if this becomes the official autopsy of another lost spring</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
