    "jays": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Blue Jays",
      "league": "MLB",
      "record": "7-9",
      "detail": "4th in AL East",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Darin Varsho, the Wisconsin kid turned homecoming king, <strong>blasted a go-ahead homer in the eighth</strong> as the Blue Jays clawed back from a late Brewers rally for a gritty 9-7 win Monday night&mdash;their first W after dropping four of five, including a brutal two-game skid to the Twins. At 7-9, they're clinging to fourth in the AL East, three games back, with that lone victory snapping the slide and bumping them to the 11th playoff seed. Vlad Guerrero Jr. stayed scorching, ripping 17 hits in 53 at-bats with a homer and five RBI, carrying this lineup like the franchise cornerstone he is&mdash;even as the bullpen wobbled under Milwaukee's late surge. No major injuries biting yet, but whispers of a blockbuster trade swirl, testing Atkins' nerve. Tonight's rubber match at American Family Field pits them against Jacob Misiorowski, the Brewers' flamethrowing phenom on a tear&mdash;<strong>can Toronto's bats exploit his rookie jitters to steal the series and ignite a climb?</strong> The East won't wait.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
