        "body": "The January chill still lingers over FedEx Field, but Washington's 5-12 Commanders clawed a measure of pride from the wreckage with a gritty 24-17 gut-punch to the Eagles on Jan. 4 &mdash; <strong>a final-day win that snapped their slide</strong> and handed Philly a bitter pill. Sitting third in the NFC East, nine games back with a modest one-game streak, this bunch ends the Dan Quinn era not with a whimper, but a defiant roar &mdash; playoff seed 14 be damned. Terry McLaurin torched secondaries all season, hauling in 1,100 yards despite the quarterback carousel, his sideline toe-taps the stuff of highlight reels amid a defense that bent but rarely broke late. Jayden Daniels' rookie flashes faded into turnovers, but whispers of a trade swirl as free agency looms. Ownership's patience? Thin as January ice. <strong>With the 2026 Draft two weeks out, eyes lock on that No. 2 pick &mdash; QB salvation or defensive dominator?</strong> This offseason rebuilds or resets; Commanders fans, brace for the board.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
